<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-10 00:47 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9805 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBN-BAGWELL-HNS &LR;      06-10 0331
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-BAGWELL-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JOSEPH DUARTE  
 c. 1999, Houston Chronicle  
CHICAGO _ It's hard to decide which side of Chicago Jeff Bagwell
likes best.
<TEXT>
<P>
   North side or south side?
</P>
<P>
   Regardless, baseballs are flying in the Windy City.
</P>
<P>
   Bagwell on Wednesday night posted his second three-home-run game
in Chicago this season, hitting his 18th, 19th and 20th of the year
in the Astros' 13-4 rout of the White Sox at Comiskey Park.
</P>
<P>
   Bagwell had three home runs April 21 across town at Wrigley
Field. In five games this season in Chicago, Bagwell has six homers
and 14 RBIs. Wednesday's was Bagwell's 17th multiple-homer game and
the third three-homer game of his career.
</P>
<P>
   He became just the 12th major-leaguer with a pair of three-homer
games in a season.
</P>
<P>
   What surprised the power-hitting first baseman the most was that
his three long balls came after an 0-for-3 start at the plate that
included a fly to right, a strikeout looking and a pop-up in foul
territory.
</P>
<P>
   ``Home runs come in cycles,'' said Bagwell, who moved into a tie
with the Cubs' Sammy Sosa for the National League lead. ``I was
having a tough game. It's kind of funny to hit three home runs
after the start I had. I wouldn't have bet on that.''
</P>
<P>
   Bagwell sent the first pitch from reliever Sean Lowe over the
left-center-field wall for a three-run homer in the sixth. He hit a
full-count solo homer to left off Bill Simas in the eighth and a
two-run shot to left off Keith Foulke on an 0-1 pitch in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   The six RBIs give him 58 for the season, tops in the NL.
</P>
<P>
   ``I go in streaks when I hit home runs,'' Bagwell said. ``My
swing is kind of unorthodox. When it's off, I'm not hitting any
home runs.''
</P>
<P>
   In 1994, Bagwell hit three home runs against Los Angeles. The
last player to have two three-homer games in a season was Mark
McGwire last season.
</P>
<P>
   There have been a total of seven three-homer games in the majors
this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
