<HEADLINE>
ATTN: NEWSPAPERS THAT RAN MAY 29 PIPELINE SAFETY STORY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED: The size of a fuel spill in 1989 near Augusta, Kan.,
was incorrectly described May 29 in a Kansas City Star article as
450,000 gallons and possibly the worst pipeline incident in state
history. In fact, when a construction crew accidentally ruptured
the pipeline operated by Kaneb Pipe Line Co. almost 50,000 gallons
of gasoline flowed out. While state officials consider it a
significant spill, others in Kansas have been larger.
</P>
</TEXT>
