<SLUG> BC-GEN-NORTHRIDGE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NORTHRIDGE AD HIRING CHALLENGED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Saying former Cal State Northridge president
Blenda Wilson disregarded the recommendations of diverse campus
entities, several university advisory board members announced
Wednesday they are requesting the recent appointment of Dick Dull
as the school's new athletic director be overturned.
</P>
<P>
   ``The decision deserves investigation and it deserves
reconsideration,'' said Lee Alpert, a board member who supported
Robert Arias as the new athletic director. ``President Wilson's
appointment of Dick Dull, with the choice of Bobby Arias still out
there, simply flies in the face of logic.''
</P>
<P>
   Seven people spoke at the press conference, which drew 18
people, all of whom are Arias supporters. Some made references to
Dull's background and the fact Dull resigned as athletic director
at Maryland in 1986 in the wake of the Len Bias cocaine death
controversy.
</P>
<P>
   The formal request, which is addressed to Governor Gray Davis,
Assembly Speaker Antonio Villaraigosa, D-Los Angeles and CSU
Chancellor Charles Reed, also claimed there was a
``misrepresentation'' by Dull to ``the San Fernando Valley
community about his experience at the University of Nebraska (He
was actually at Nebraska-Kearny).''
</P>
<P>
   In fact, Dull never represented himself to anyone at CSUN as
being the athletic director at the University of Nebraska.
</P>
<P>
   Alpert said Wilson's choice of Dull went against the
recommendation from the athletic director search committee and
CSUN's head coaches.
</P>
<P>
   ``From what I know,'' Alpert said, ``it was unanimous. I would
assume that included the two coaches (on the committee).''
</P>
<P>
   A member of the search committee, who wished to remain
anonymous, said that is not true.
</P>
<P>
   ``We weren't allowed to select anybody,'' said the committee
member. ``We were commissioned to select four people to recommend
to president Wilson.''
</P>
<P>
   Sam Jankovich, CSUN's interim athletic director who will
relinquish his duties when Dull takes over July 1, confirmed there
was not a unanimous vote of the coaching staff or the search
committee.
</P>
<P>
   Jankovich also said he disagreed with Arias' supporters holding
a press conference to decry the selection of Dull.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it's proper,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
