pelt of some rare mountain sheep. The thing is almost obscenely
sexy, a vaguely naughty artifact from a more swinging age that
makes you want to exclaim, in a bad impersonation of Austin Powers,
``Oh, behave!'' By Rick Marin.
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOOR-FLOORS (Undated) _ An outdoor floor used to be forever.
To install a terrace, patio or deck meant waiting on professionals,
with their own inscrutable timetables. Now, with do-it-yourself
kits and loose-lay flooring, you can just about bring home the deck
and put out the lounge chairs. By Marianne Rohrlich.
</P>
