<P>
   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _ LUFKIN, Texas _ Computer magnate and
multibillionaire Bill Gates is alleged to have said that if the car
industry had kept up with technology like the computer industry
has, we would all be driving $25 cars that got 1,000 miles to the
gallon. This bit of whimsy, sent to me by a friend, shows what
would happen if indeed Detroit built cars the same way personal
computers are.(Ernest Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily
News) MOVED. EMBARGOED for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ Newspaper people, apparently everywhere but New
York, have a sense of humor. At least that's what The New York
Post's mention of my recent column leads me to believe. (Gary
Borders is editor and publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel.)
MOVED. EMBARGOED for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ This column will not move today.
(Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of the Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Lt. Gov. Rick Perry got fairly
high marks for his first session following Democrat Bob Bullock as
presiding officer of the Texas Senate. A look at who said what and
how his term shaped the Senate. (McNeely, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ . (John Young is opinion page
editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald).
</P>
