<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   RESTAURANTS-NOISE _ That sleek industrial look so popular in
restaurants these days has a sometimes intended, sometimes not
effect: noise. Restaurant owners say an energetic buzz can draw
younger customers, yet some are taking steps to cut down on the
commotion. Floataway Cafe, for example, is installing carpet in
early July because noise is the most common complaint they get.
(Lee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35. MOVED. ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   BAPTISTS _ ATLANTA _ In the days before their annual meeting in
Atlanta, Southern Baptists plan to blitz the city with evangelism,
door-to-door and in revival-style worship. This comes at a time
when the denomination recently admitted losing members for the
first time in decades. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (l) Lifestyle categories.
</P>
