   JERRY-GARCIA (San Francisco) _ Whether you are a rabid fan or
not, ``Garcia: An American Life'' (Viking; $34.95), by Blair
Jackson, is a fascinating look at one of the more complex and
influential personalities to emerge from the '60's maelstrom, a
musician that Bob Dylan claimed ``had no equal.'' The book is due
to be released this summer. By CRAIG MARINE.
