<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Is it in the genes? As he prepared
to take his presidential campaign outside of Texas for the first
time, Gov. George W. Bush tied himself into a no-new-taxes knot
just like the one that brought down his father. He blew the
possibility of making ``compassionate conservatism'' look like a
creative new deal, not just another rigid, stingy GOP approach to
governing. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
