his presidential bid next week on the steps of the Smith County
courthouse in Carthage, Tenn., his ancestral home. Gore supporters
hope the announcement jump starts a campaign beset by a lack of
focus and voter perception that Gore himself is kind of a bore.
Republicans are heartened by polls showing Texas Gov. George W.
Bush and Elizabeth Dole both leading Gore, but they do not see Gore
as a pushover. By DAN FREEDMAN.
