   CHINA-DISSIDENT (Beijing) _ A businessman and former government
planner who distributed a pro-democracy manifesto last year was
sentenced Thursday to four years in prison, the latest in a series
of harsh steps taken against dissidents in the last month. By Eric
Eckholm.
</P>
