 &HT;    Now, the revolution has led to another first: physicians are
clamoring to join unions as never before. Courted by everyone from
the American Federation of Teachers to the International
Association of Machinists, doctors are beginning to unionize across
the country. And they are being welcomed with open arms.
 &HT;    The Service Employees International Union, the nation's
fastest-growing labor coalition, pledged in March to spend $1
million this year to organize the nation's 600,000 doctors. Even
the United Food and Commercial Workers union has gotten into the
act, seeking to expand its base by enrolling doctors disaffected
