 ART ADV.: Photos with COMPUTERS-SPEECH and AUTOS-REVIEW are being
transmitted to NYT Photo Service subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Roy Greene  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-DRASKOVIC (Belgrade) _ As head of the biggest opposition
party in Serbia, Vuk Draskovic is mentioned as one politician who
could replace Slobodan Milosevic. While many praise Draskovic's
blunt and often courageous honesty, they just as often bemoan his
unpredictability and volatility. By Kevin Cullen. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOLS-SHAME (Fort Worth, Texas) _ A Texas policy that sets up
low-performing schools for public embarrassment appears to help
many of them improve. Other states are looking at the power of
shame. By Beth Daley. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JACOBY-COLUMN (Undated) _ In the past month, 12 Boston-area cab
drivers have been attacked by armed passengers. The media response
has been all but nonexistent. By Jeff Jacoby.
</P>
<P>
   ELLIS-COLUMN (Undated) -- An important shift in the employment
game is under way. Talent is going to the Web. By John Ellis. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE &LR;   &UR; (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ The American Horticultural Society
holds its annual conference. By Carol Stocker. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-TOURS (Undated) -- June is the month of wine and roses _
and garden tours, courses, and lectures. By Ruth Foster.
</P>
<P>
   CHILDCARE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Parents of an only child face a
challenge of being too involved in their child's activities and not
being involved enough. By Barbara Meltz. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY-COLUMN (Undated) _ After 40 years, love may no longer
rage like a bonfire, but the heat generated by glances of
