series and will also look at coach Jeff Van Gundy's situation _
despite all the rumors about his possible departure, a victory on
Friday puts him in the driver's seat for next season. By Selena
Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-PACERS (Undated) _ An analytical look at the Pacers. All
told, they look like the Knicks of old: slow, plodding, lethargic.
By Judy Battista.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ When the Mets traded for Bobby Bonilla
in the off-season a lot of people scratched their heads. He was
starting to get old, he had spent much of 1998 injured and it was
very unclear whether he could still cover enough ground to play in
the outfield. Now he has quickly become a big distraction in the
clubhouse and the Mets may now be forced to cut him and then pay
him all the money they still owe him. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKEES (undated) _ The Yankees are not the team they were a
year ago, although they are back in first place. With the trading
deadline six weeks away, a look at who the Yankees have in the
minor leagues and which of those players might form an attractive
package that would bring the Yankees some help in return. By Buster
Olney.
</P>
