   JOHNSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The late, lamented comedian Jimmy Durante had an
expression that fits what's happening to that long-standing Texas
tradition called Juneteenth. Confronted with instances of people
imitating him or responding to some funny line of his, Durante
would grumble: ``Everybody wants to get into de act.'' So it seems
with the June 19 observances that most African-Americans in Texas
have considered their own peculiar institution. By CECIL JOHNSON.
Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
