   BIZBOOKS-REVIEWS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ If you love roller-coaster investing, consider the
IPO. Buying stock in a company's initial public offering is not for
the weak-hearted, financial writer Tom Taulli says. But the
potential to make money is astronomical. ``Investing in IPOs can be
a wild ride,'' admits Taulli, who writes about such investing for
Barron's and other print media, appears on CNN and CNBC and writes
columns for online investment publications such as Microsoft
Investor. But Taulli adds that some sense of order can be brought
to the risky investment through patience and research. He shares
his expertise on the subject in ``Investing In IPOs'' (Bloomberg
Press, 264 pages). By TERESA McUSIC. Story has moved in ``f''
financial category. &QL; 
