<HEADER>
A0566 &Cx1f; taf-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SEASON-MOVIE-REVIEW-N     06-10 0414
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SEASON-MOVIE-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`OUT OF SEASON': A PROMISING BEGINNING 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: Production notes are at end of review.) 
(mk) 
 By LAWRENCE VAN GELDER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Will Micki and Roberta become lovers? Will Micki and Roberta be
together when ``Out of Season'' reaches its conclusion?
</P>
<P>
   Never for a moment are the answers in doubt in this serious,
competent and unsurprising debut film, made by Jeannette Buck as a
thesis project for her master's degree in fine arts at Ohio
University.
</P>
<P>
   Set in Cape May, N.J., in the months after the tourists have
gone, the story, written by Kim McNabb, a co-producer, tells of a
lesbian, Micki Silva (Carol Monda), a wary, rolling stone of a
professional photographer who comes to town to take care of her
kindly old uncle, Charlie (Dennis Fecteau).
</P>
<P>
   Micki has only reluctantly accepted the assignment from her
family. She is not the epitome of warmth, says she knows how to
cook only one dish and is uncomfortable attending to a dying man,
even one who has his good days.
</P>
<P>
   But when Micki lays eyes on Roberta (Joy Kelly), a lesbian who
works as a short-order cook at a coffee shop and is also a devoted
friend of Charlie's, she is determined to establish a relationship.
</P>
<P>
   Micki and the 40-ish Roberta, who is both warm and wise, spar
through a good part of the film. Roberta senses that Micki doesn't
plan to stay around for long and isn't eager to encourage her. But
Micki presses on, while the wheezing, coughing, bearded Charlie,
like a benevolent old Santa Claus, referees, manipulates and
ultimately blesses their relationship.
</P>
<P>
   Apparently working on a shoestring budget, Ms. Buck takes
advantage of the physical and natural attractiveness of Cape May,
avoids easy sentiment, resists the impulse to transform the
difficult Micki into a sudden bundle of radiant charm and lets Ms.
Kelly shine as a worthy object of love.
</P>
<P>
   ``Out of Season,'' which opens oday at the Quad Cinema, is a
modest movie but a promising beginning.
</P>
<P>
   PRODUCTION NOTES:
</P>
<P>
   `OUT OF SEASON'
</P>
<P>
   Produced and directed by Jeanette Buck; written by Kim McNabb;
director of photography, Ed Talaver; edited by Sharon Teo; music by
Miki Navazio, with Janine DeLorenzo and Kenni Feinberg; released by
IMJ Productions and Jour de Fete Films. Running time: 85 minutes.
This film is not rated.
</P>
<P>
   With: Carol Monda (Micki), Joy Kelly (Roberta), Dennis Fecteau
(Charlie), Nancy Daly (Shelley) and Rusty Clauss (Jane).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-10-99 1711EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
