</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMPARE AND CONTRAST &LR;
</P>
<P>
   On his way into the Washington Square Bar &AMP; Grill the other day,
 &UR; Jim Schock &LR;  overheard two gentlemen in conversation:
</P>
<P>
   ``Mine's smaller than yours,'' said one.
</P>
<P>
   ``No,'' said the other, ``mine is smaller, definitely.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Let's hold them side by side and see.''
</P>
<P>
   Schock said he couldn't resist eavesdropping further. The gents
were discussing their cell phones.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Rolling Stone reports on the World Music Awards recently in
Monaco, co-hosted by  &UR; Pamela Anderson Lee &LR;  and  &UR; Damon Wayans &LR; .
Commenting on his co-host's recent breast implant removal surgery,
Wayans said, ``If they were bigger before, I don't know how she
stood up. She must have had a kickstand or something.''
</P>
<P>
   _ A comparison of the Napa Valley to the Hamptons in Sunday's
New York Times reveals that  &UR; Tom Waits &LR;  is going to sing ``Here
Comes the Bride'' when  &UR; Sofia Coppola &LR;  marries director  &UR; Spike &LR; 
 &UR; Jonze &LR;  at the Coppolas' place in Rutherford this summer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Everybody in New York has ``Run, Hillary, Run'' bumper
stickers on their cars, reports  &UR; Baird Jones &LR; . Democrats have them
on their rear bumpers; Republicans on the front.
</P>
<P>
   _ Regarding Paris in Las Vegas:  &UR; Bonnie Jones &LR;  reports that on a
recent trip she was unable to find pate anywhere in Las Vegas, but
did locate the ``largest Krispy Kreme doughnuts factory store in
the West.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Dennis Bradley &LR; , a recent graduate of Duke University's Fuqua
School of Business, is still watching over the place: That
``Oprah'' quote cited in Personals and attributed to  &UR; Ted Turner &LR; 
by People magazine was actually said by a student speaker,  &UR; Craig &LR; 
 &UR; Crawford &LR; .
