<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-USCHOOP-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THURSTON CHOOSES USC OVER OREGON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC has used its final basketball scholarship by
signing 6-foot-4, 200-pound shooting guard Malachi Thurston of
Oakland.
</P>
<P>
   Thurston played this past season at The Hotchkiss School, a prep
school in Lakeville, Conn. He averaged 24 points, nine rebounds and
three assists per game last season.
</P>
<P>
   He selected USC over Oregon. Thurston played high school
basketball at Marin Academy in Oakland. Because he committed after
the signing period, Thurston cannot sign a letter of intent.
</P>
<P>
   He instead signed a nonbinding scholarship agreement, which
means he is not bound to the university.
</P>
<P>
   __ Mokeski interviews: Former Kansas University and Milwaukee
Bucks basketball player Paul Mokeski has interviewed for the
assistant coaching position vacated when Joe Callero left in April
to become head coach at the University of Puget Sound. Mokeski
played at Kansas from 1976-79.
</P>
</TEXT>
