<P>
   &UR; PUC _ &LR;  Getting the wiring fixed inside your home is about to
get more expensive. State regulators today approved a plan
supported by Pacific Bell to increase inside wiring insurance to
$1.20 per month from 60 cents per month. The ruling could also mean
more increases down the road because it also recategorizes inside
wiring as a fully competitive service. Pac Bell can raise rates
more easily on competitive services than on regulated ones. Other
rates were also affected by yesterday's ruling. Pacific Bell can
now raise the maximum fee on a collect call to $1.60 from 95 cents
and on a person-to-person collect call to $4 from $2.95. By Deborah
Solomon
</P>
