   &UR; VIRUS  &LR; _ W32ExplorerZip.worm, a malicious code patterned after
Melissa, is spreading quickly and delivering a more devastating
payload. The e-mail worm, which deletes files, has been reported in
the United States, Germany and France. The virus spreads by using
information in Microsoft's Outlook, Outlook Express and Exchange.
By Jon Swartz
</P>
