<HEADLINE>
TROJANS TO PLAY AUBURN TWICE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC has reached a two-game agreement to play
Auburn in football during the 2002 and 2003 seasons.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans will play Auburn at the Coliseum on Aug. 31, 2002,
then travel to play the Tigers in Alabama on Aug. 30, 2003. CBS has
expressed interest in televising the 2003 game.
</P>
<P>
   ``In 2002 and 2003, we get an extra game and we also wanted an
intersectional game,'' said USC associate athletic director Daryl
Gross.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans will play 12 games in each of those seasons.
</P>
<P>
   USC is also close to signing a contract for a two-game series
with Brigham Young for the 2003 and 2004 seasons. The Trojans would
play BYU at the Coliseum on Sept. 6, 2003, and at BYU on Sept. 4,
2004. Another possibility being discussed is a three-game series
with Wyoming starting in 2002.
</P>
<P>
   __ Morton hired: USC has officially hired Steve Morton as its
tight- ends coach. Morton was the offensive-line coach at
Washington under Jim Lambright. He served as a volunteer coach at
USC during spring practice.
</P>
<P>
   Morton had hoped to land an offensive-line coaching position
before deciding to accept an offer from USC coach Paul Hackett. He
begins working full-time on July 1. Morton replaces assistant head
coach Larry Petroff, who will concentrate on administrative duties.
</P>
</TEXT>
