<SLUG> BC-TECH-PARK-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BY GREGORY J. WILCOX 
</HEADLINE>
 
$40million business park planned for Moorpark 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOORPARK _ Hoping to capitalize on growth in the high-technology
sector, a Long Beach-based developer will build a $40 million
business park on 33 acres along the Moorpark Freeway.
</P>
<P>
   Cypress Land Co. recently bought the parcel from a family trust
and plans to start construction during the first quarter of next
year. The purchase price was not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   The project, called the Moorpark Corporate Center, will have
more than 500,000 square feet of space in a series of buildings
ranging in size from 15,000 square feet to 120,000 square feet.
</P>
<P>
   It will be at the southwest corner of the freeway and New Los
Angeles Avenue.
</P>
<P>
   Cypress officials could not be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Tingus, vice president of the San Fernando Valley office of
the Seeley Co., which brokered the deal, said Cypress is hoping to
capture some spillover of business from companies in the West San
Fernando Valley or east Ventura County that want to expand but
cannot find suitable sites in those locales.
</P>
<P>
   Seeley will start looking for tenants in the first few months of
next year, Tingus said.
</P>
<P>
   Lease rates have not been set, but they will be less than what
companies pay along the Ventura Freeway corridor. That area, which
stretches from Calabasas to Camarillo and is known as the 101 Tech
Corridor, has become a magnet for high-tech and biotech companies.
The most well-known is probably Amgen Inc., the world's largest
biotechnology company, which is headquartered near the Ventura
Freeway a few miles west of the Moorpark Freeway.
</P>
<P>
   There should not be a shortage of potential tenants because the
Moorpark market is short on buildings larger than 40,000 square
feet, Tingus said.
</P>
<P>
   ``That type of product is the kind we are finding the high-tech
users are going for,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Seeley broker John DeGrinis said vacancy rates in the Moorpark
area are running about 6 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Cypress has built and owns more than 2.5 million square feet of
industrial office parks in Southern California.!
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
